<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: SAN CLEMENTE MAN WINS $31,725 SURFING PRIZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Christian Fletcher of San Clemente earned the largest first-place prize in 
surfing history Sunday by winning the $100,000 Body Glove Surf Bout at Camp 
Pendleton's Lower Trestles. 
</P>
<P>
Fletcher, 19, won $31,725 by defeating North Hollywood's Joey Jenkins, 
Cardiff's Colin Smith (24th seed) and San Clemente's Noah Budroe (seventh seed) 
in the final. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Dino Andino of San Clemente finished fifth, maintaining his overall 
ratings lead with three tournaments remaining on the 11-city Bud Light U.S. Pro 
Surfing Tour. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Stewart of Hawaii won the largest payoff ($5,000) ever in bodyboarding by 
defeating Irvine's Pat Caldwell, Imperial Beach's Jackie Fisher and Honolulu's 
Ben Severson in the final of the Easy Rider Bodyboard Division. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego defeated Cal State Dominguez Hills, 2-1, to win the 
U.S. International tournament with a 2-0 record. The Toreros (4-1) beat Cal, 
6-2, on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
In the second half against Dominguez Hills, USD's Tom Crane took a pass from 
Trong Nguyen (named the tournament's outstanding defensive player), went 
one-on-one against the goalie and scored the winning goal off the right post. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Pearson, who scored the first goal, was named the offensive player of the 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Cal defeated USIU, 2-1, in the other match. Chris George scored for the Gulls. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego opened its season with a 3-0 victory over USIU (0-2). Felicia 
Faro, Toni Krumme and Katy Dulock scored for the Tritons. 
</P>
<P>
YACHTING 
</P>
<P>
The San Diego Yacht Club's Chris Calkins skippered Flambouyant to victory in 
the SDYC's Navy Trophy race on San Diego Bay with a time of two hours 18.33 
seconds. 
</P>
