<HEADLINE>
<P>
GLEMP'S REMARKS ON AUSCHWITZ 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The editorial certainly is a new low. How dare you put the Polish cardinal down 
for speaking the truth! How dare the Jews try to tell the Catholic Church or 
Poland where it can or cannot place a convent. A convent which houses nuns 
praying for, among others, dead Jews. What harm is the convent doing? What evil 
thing? In the first place, the convent is on the edge of Auschwitz, not smack 
dab in the heart of it. 
</P>
<P>
Second, aren't we talking about Polish land? What would the U.S. think if a 
foreign group came here and tried to dictate where we could put what. Americans 
would go through the roof and rightly so. The Jews who were beaten were 
illegally trespassing. They were lucky that was all that happened to them. 
After all, Palestinian children protesting Israeli occupation of their land 
have been shot! 
</P>
<P>
I think the Jews would serve their public image, not to mention moral ethics, 
if they would leave the nuns to their prayers and concentrated a lot more 
attention on the holocaust they are creating in the Middle East. 
</P>
<P>
GERALD ROEMER 
</P>
