<HEADLINE>
<P>
RANCHO BERNARDO MAN, 83, FOUND DEAD IN ALPINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An 83-year-old Rancho Bernardo man who had been missing since Thursday was 
found dead Sunday morning in Alpine. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Benjamin Ratner was discovered on a dirt road about a mile south of 
a dead end at the eastern end of Alpine Boulevard, according to sheriff's 
spokesman Sgt. Chris Von Olmhousen. Ratner's 1977 Cadillac Seville was found 
about 200 feet away, stuck in the dirt, Von Olmhousen said. 
</P>
<P>
Though the cause of Ratner's death is still undetermined, homicide detectives 
said there were no signs of foul play. 
</P>
<P>
Sheriff's deputies responding to a call about a body on the road made the 
discovery at 10:30 a.m. Sunday, and quickly determined that the deceased man 
was Ratner. 
</P>
<P>
Ratner's family had reported him missing at noon Thursday, after he failed to 
pick up his wife, Bernice, at a beauty parlor, as planned. 
</P>
<P>
The family had set up a telephone hot line to receive information about Ratner 
and were offering a reward for information leading to his safe return. 
</P>
