<P>
Iran's Parliament condemned 186 U.S. congressmen for endorsing Iranian 
resistance groups and declared that their action will unleash unspecified 
"consequences." Tehran Radio quoted Parliament Speaker Mahdi Karrubi as saying 
that "U.S. leaders will take the wish of overthrowing the Islamic Republic to 
their graves." In a letter addressed to Secretary of State James A. Baker III, 
121 Democrats and 65 Republicans last week warned the Administration against 
"continuing to speculate and hope for the miraculous emergence of moderates 
from within the present ruling clique" in Iran. 
