<P>
More than a thousand worshipers cheered as Father George A. Stallings Jr. 
called for a boycott of businesses that advertise in the Washington Post, and 
he denounced allegations published in the Post that he had a sexual 
relationship 12 years ago with an altar boy. "We're going to get you, 
Washington Post, because of your sleazy journalism, because of your obsession 
to create a story where there is no story," the dissident Roman Catholic priest 
told a packed auditorium. Post Managing Editor Leonard Downie Jr. later said in 
reply: "We believe we have treated the Rev. Stallings fairly." 
