<HEADLINE>
<P>
NAVRATILOVA-MANDLIKOVA DEFEAT SHRIVER-FERNANDEZ IN DOUBLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Martina Navratilova, who won 19 Grand Slam doubles titles with Pam Shriver as a 
partner, teamed with Hana Mandlikova to take the U.S. Open women's doubles 
title Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova and Mandlikova beat Shriver and Mary Jo Fernandez, 5-7, 6-4, 6-4. 
Navratilova and Shriver split last month. 
</P>
<P>
"We've had one of the greatest partnerships of all time together," said 
Navratilova, who is expected to team with Shriver next month in the Federation 
Cup. "I don't know if I'll commit to anybody for a full year. 
</P>
<P>
"I had a feeling that the crowd felt I had wronged Pam, that it was my fault. 
Everything I did was above board." 
</P>
<P>
Shriver and Fernandez never had played together and became a team just moments 
before the entry deadline. 
</P>
<P>
"If this was a marriage, I'd call it a trial separation," Navratilova said 
early last week. "I thought Pam needed time to sort out her career. She was so 
scattered." 
</P>
<P>
Said Shriver: "Our schedules didn't work out well this year. It was also at a 
time I was questioning my dedication. 
</P>
<P>
"I guess it was a time she thought she would give me a kick in my pants, three 
weeks before the Open. But I understand it because, besides friendship, it's a 
business and a partnership." 
</P>
<P>
Navratilova and Mandlikova blew three match points before clinching the title 
on Navratilova's overhead. 
</P>
<P>
For Mandlikova, who has won four Grand Slam singles titles, it was her first 
major doubles victory. 
</P>
<P>
"Winning with Martina is a great honor," Mandlikova said. "I enjoyed it. As to 
the future, it is up to her, not me. 
</P>
<P>
"I felt something was going on between Pam and Martina and that I needed to 
prove something. Then, on one of the changeovers, I said, 'I don't need to 
prove anything. Just win the match.' " 
</P>
</TEXT>
