<HEADLINE>
<P>
FLETCHER TAKES SURFING'S TOP PURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAMP PENDLETON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Christian Fletcher of San Clemente earned the largest first-place prize money 
in surfing history Sunday at Lower Trestles State Beach by winning the $100,000 
Body Glove Surf Bout. 
</P>
<P>
The unseeded Fletcher, 19, won $31,725 by defeating North Hollywood's Joey 
Jenkins, Cardiff's Colin Smith and San Clemente's Noah Budroe in the final. 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Dino Andino of San Clemente finished fifth, but held on to the 
overall ratings lead with three tournaments remaining on the 11-city Bud Light 
U.S. Pro Surfing Tour. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Stewart of Hawaii won the largest payoff ($5,000) in bodyboarding history 
by defeating Irvine's Pat Caldwell, Imperial Beach's Jackie Fisher and 
Honolulu's Ben Severson in the final of the Easy Rider Bodyboard Division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
