<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAVIS NAMED ANGEL OF WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Left fielder Chili Davis, who had nine hits, a home run and four RBIs in 27 
at-bats last week (.333 average), is The Times' Orange County Edition Angel of 
the Week. 
</P>
<P>
Davis, whose 13-game hitting streak was broken in Saturday night's 8-5 victory 
over the Boston Red Sox, has raised his batting average almost 40 points in the 
past month to .270. 
</P>
<P>
The Times will donate $200 in Davis' name to the Boys and Girls Clubs of Orange 
County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
