<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Profile of AT&amp;T Stockholders Changing: Retirees still make up the biggest 
block of American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. shareholders, but those who 
have bought stock since the Bell System breakup tend to be younger and more 
interested in growth, the company says in a new survey. AT&amp;T is the most 
widely held stock in the nation at 2.6 million shareholders. Among survey 
findings: 70% of shareholders are 50 or older; 28% are under 50, compared with 
15% in 1983; and shareholders still rate security as their top reason for 
owning AT&amp;T stock, although growth has moved into second place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
