<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stealth Bomber Designers Honored: The Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics 
has cited John F. Cashen, James E. Kinnu, Irving T. Waaland and the late John 
Paterno for designing the B-2 Stealth bomber. Cashen, a former Bell Labs and 
Hughes Aircraft scientist, is a specialist in low radar observability and was 
chiefly responsible for the ability of the B-2 to elude enemy radar. Waaland 
was the aerodynamicist credited with designing the B-2's unusual flying wing 
configuration. Kinnu is a military electronics expert and Paterno was general 
manager of the program. 
</P>
