<P>
SIMI ROOFING CONTRACTOR ARRESTED ON SUSPICION OF MOLESTING 2 GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Simi Valley roofing contractor has been arrested on suspicion of felony child 
molesting in which two young girls were victims, authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
Richard George Grabowski, 35, was arrested Friday afternoon after a two-week 
investigation, Simi Valley police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police declined to release details of the investigation or circumstances of the 
alleged molesting but reported that the victims were two local girls, aged 11 
and 12. 
</P>
<P>
The investigation was prompted by a report of the alleged molesting of the 
girls on Aug. 26, police said. On Friday, detectives conducting a surveillance 
of Grabowski arrested him at 4:20 p.m. near his home on Walnut Street near Tapo 
Canyon Road. 
</P>
<P>
Grabowski this morning remained in the Ventura County Sheriff's Department jail 
in Ventura in lieu of $250,000 bail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
